The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Vimta Labs Ltd decided to increase the limit of foreign institutional investors? (FII) investment from 24 per cent to 49 per cent at an extraordinary general meeting held recently. The company has authorised the board to allot 8,25,432 equity shares of Rs 10 each at a price of Rs 950 per share to various funds. Mauritius-based Voyager Fund Mauritius Ltd and Minivet Ltd would be allotted 2,33,079 equity shares and 93,231 shares respectively and 2,33,079 shares would be given to India Fund Inc.

 Allianz Securities Ltd has allotted 24 lakh equity shares of Rs 6 each to Allianz Capital amp; Management Services Ltd and Rajasthan Global Securities Ltd upon conversion of an equal number of warrants. Fifteen lakh shares were allotted to Allianz Capital amp; Management Services and Rajasthan Global received 9 lakh shares upon conversion of the warrants.

 Hewlett-Packard India has launched Call amp; Click programme, enabling customers to buy HP products any time and from anywhere. They can buy HP products and take advantage of bundled offers and accessories by visiting the ?HP Call amp; Click Advantage? online store.

 GoAir has been appointed the official carrier for the upcoming India-England one-day international cricket series in April. The airline will carry both the teams and will operate special flights. 

 Air Deccan has moved up to the third position in terms of market share, nearly doubling it from seven per cent to 13.5 per cent. The company flies to 53 destinations plying 215 flights a day.

 IVRCL Infrastructures amp; Projects Ltd is setting up a steel fabrication and galvanisation unit at an estimated cost of Rs 10 crore for manufacturing transmission line tower parts. The 23-acre unit is expected to commence production during the third quarter of 2006-07.

 Delhi-based Media Video Ltd will acquire real estate development company Smart Buildwell Pvt Ltd for Rs 22 crore. The board has also approved an increase in the limit of investment by foreign institutional investors to 24 per cent.

 Pepe Jeans London has launched a specially imported range from Europe for men and women called ?The One of 1? collection in Calcutta. The new collection in cotton is for summer and has jeans, jackets, T-shirts and skirts.

 Film production and distribution company Shree Ashtavinayak Cine Vision Ltd is targeting revenues of Rs 52 crore for the financial year ending March against Rs 26.69 crore in the year-ago period.

